    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-01T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1723</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-01T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1915, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.30 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>256. Events point to Italy’s decisive step soon. The promised attendance of King
                    of Italy and Minister of War at Garibaldi celebration at Quarto on 5th
                    considered indicative of such decision, as are orders recently placed for large
                    stores, including 10,000 artillery horses.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
